I'm Chairman and CEO of the Omni Group, which I founded with Tim Wood and Wil Shipley. I'm a computer geek at heart, and continue to contribute directly to all of Omni's products as an interface designer and software engineer, most recently working on the iPad editions of OmniGraffle, OmniFocus, OmniOutliner, and OmniPlan. Before founding Omni in 1992, I worked as a contract application programmer for NeXT, a systems programmer for the University of Washington, and a systems administrator for both the Center for Process Analytical Chemistry and Statistical Sciences, Inc.

During my early career I developed software for over eighteen operating systems, but since finding the NeXT / Mac / iOS platform I've been happy to focus on the platform which I feel makes our team the most productive. I've contributed free source code to the net throughout my career, and have used both emacs and vi daily for over twenty-five years (avoiding flame wars with either camp). I live in Seattle with my wife, our two daughters, and two cats.
